@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Angolos" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile located next (either horizontally or
diagonally) to the last linked tile, or the starting tile if you start
a game. If the move is possible, a coloured line of the same colour as
the starting tile will link the two tiles together.

  Note that once you have passed on a tile, you cannot go back to it,
unless it is the starting tile, but beware: if you didn't go to all
the tiles on the board, going to the starting tile will end the game.
By the way, trapping yourself in a dead-end, or on a tile surrounded
by already linked tiles, will also end the game.

  When you complete the game, in other words, you moved on all the
tiles and got back to the starting tile, the game will display how many
angles you made and if it exceeds the previous biggest number of angles
('High Angles') made on that board, the game will tell you so and the
biggest number of angles will be updated.

  You can resize the game board by clicking on the '+' and '-' buttons
that are located in the 'Y' shaped pattern at the right of the game
board. Those buttons will either increase or decrease the higher part,
lower part or middle width (the widest part) of the game board. As you
change the game board size, the 'High Angles' displayed on the lower
right position of the game window, indicates the biggest number of
angles made in that particular game board size.

  You can change the starting tile's colour as well as the colour of
the links, if there are any, by clicking on any tile that is not
located next to the last linked tile.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}Restart@{ub} button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

